---
import ArticleLayout from '../../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: "quick-verdict", label: "Quick Verdict" },
  { id: "head-to-head", label: "Head-to-Head Table" },
  { id: "scheduling", label: "Scheduling & Dispatch" },
  { id: "crm", label: "CRM & Pipeline" },
  { id: "pricing-compare", label: "Pricing Comparison" },
  { id: "true-cost", label: "True Cost Analysis" },
  { id: "choose-this-if", label: "Choose This If" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQ" }
];
const faqItems = [
  { q: "Can I switch from Housecall Pro to Jobber (or vice versa)?", a: "Yes. Both platforms support CSV data export and import. The migration typically takes 1-2 weeks including data transfer and team retraining." },
  { q: "Which has a better mobile app?", a: "Both have strong mobile apps. Housecall Pro's app is slightly more feature-rich (includes review requests and marketing tools). Jobber's app is cleaner and faster for basic field operations." },
  { q: "Do either offer call tracking?", a: "Neither has built-in call tracking. Both integrate with CallRail and similar tools. If call tracking is critical, consider Workiz instead." },
  { q: "Which is better for a plumbing company?", a: "Both work well for plumbing. Jobber is slightly better for emergency/on-demand scheduling. Housecall Pro is better if you want automated review requests after jobs." }
];
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Housecall Pro vs Jobber (2026): HVAC Head-to-Head — HVAC Software Hub"
  description="We compared Housecall Pro and Jobber across 7 categories for HVAC companies."
  canonicalPath="/hvac/crm/housecall-pro-vs-jobber"
  category="Comparisons"
  publishDate="2026-02-19"
  readTime="10 min read"
  intent="BOFU"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  faqItems={faqItems}
>
<div class="container py-8">
        <div class="flex gap-12">
          <article class="flex-1 min-w-0 max-w-3xl">

            <div id="quick-verdict" class="mt-8">
              <div class="verdict-strip">
                <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
                  <strong>Quick Verdict:</strong> Choose <strong>Jobber</strong> if you want the simplest, most affordable CRM for a small team (1-5 techs). Choose <strong>Housecall Pro</strong> if you want more marketing features (online booking, review automation) and are willing to pay slightly more.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="head-to-head" class="mt-8">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">Head-to-Head Comparison</h2>
              <table class="comparison-table">
<thead><tr>
  <th>Category</th>
  <th>Housecall Pro</th>
  <th>Jobber</th>
  <th>Winner</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td>Scheduling & Dispatch</td>
  <td>Drag-and-drop, real-time</td>
  <td>Drag-and-drop, clean UI</td>
  <td>Tie</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>CRM & Pipeline</td>
  <td>Basic pipeline + review requests</td>
  <td>Client hub + quote follow-ups</td>
  <td>HCP (reviews)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Online Booking</td>
  <td>Built-in, customizable</td>
  <td>Built-in, client portal</td>
  <td>HCP</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Mobile App</td>
  <td>Feature-rich, includes marketing</td>
  <td>Clean, fast, field-focused</td>
  <td>Tie</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Integrations</td>
  <td>QuickBooks, Mailchimp, Zapier</td>
  <td>QuickBooks, Stripe, Zapier</td>
  <td>Tie</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Reporting</td>
  <td>Good on Essentials+</td>
  <td>Basic on lower tiers</td>
  <td>HCP</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Ease of Use</td>
  <td>Easy (8/10)</td>
  <td>Very easy (9/10)</td>
  <td>Jobber</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
            </div>

            <div id="scheduling" class="mt-10">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3">Scheduling & Dispatch</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Both platforms offer drag-and-drop scheduling with real-time technician status updates. Housecall Pro's dispatch board is slightly more visual with color-coded job types. Jobber's calendar is cleaner and faster to navigate. For most HVAC companies under 10 techs, both are more than adequate. <strong>Verdict: Tie.</strong>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="crm" class="mt-8">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3">CRM & Pipeline Management</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Jobber's Client Hub lets customers approve quotes, schedule appointments, and pay invoices online — it is one of the best client-facing portals in the industry. Housecall Pro counters with built-in review request automation that sends Google review requests after completed jobs. If getting more reviews is a priority, HCP wins. If you want a better customer self-service experience, Jobber wins. <strong>Verdict: Housecall Pro (for reviews).</strong>
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="pricing-compare" class="mt-8">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">Pricing Comparison</h2>
              <table class="comparison-table">
<thead><tr>
  <th>Tier</th>
  <th>Housecall Pro</th>
  <th>Jobber</th>
  <th>Difference</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td>Entry</td>
  <td>$59/mo (Basic, 1 user)</td>
  <td>$39/mo (Core, 1 user)</td>
  <td>Jobber saves $20/mo</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Mid</td>
  <td>$149/mo (Essentials, 5 users)</td>
  <td>$129/mo (Connect, 5 users)</td>
  <td>Jobber saves $20/mo</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Growth</td>
  <td>Custom (MAX, 8+ users)</td>
  <td>$249/mo (Grow, 15 users)</td>
  <td>Jobber is transparent</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
            </div>

            <div id="true-cost" class="mt-8">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">True Cost Analysis (Including Add-Ons)</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/70 mb-4">
                The sticker price does not tell the full story. HVAC companies typically need review management and marketing tools. Here is the true monthly cost for a 5-user team:
              </p>
              <table class="comparison-table">
<thead><tr>
  <th>Line Item</th>
  <th>Housecall Pro</th>
  <th>Jobber</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td>Base plan (5 users)</td>
  <td>$149/mo (Essentials)</td>
  <td>$129/mo (Connect)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Review management</td>
  <td>Included</td>
  <td>+$75/mo (NiceJob or similar)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Marketing/email</td>
  <td>Included (basic)</td>
  <td>+$29/mo (Mailchimp)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td>Total monthly cost</td>
  <td>$149/mo</td>
  <td>$233/mo</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
              <div class="verdict-strip">
                <p class="text-sm">
                  <strong>Key insight:</strong> When you factor in the add-ons that HVAC companies actually need (review requests + basic marketing), Jobber costs <strong>$84/mo more</strong> than Housecall Pro. The sticker price advantage disappears. This is the most important comparison most review sites miss.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div id="choose-this-if" class="mt-10">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-2xl mb-4">Choose This If...</h2>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
                  <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3 text-primary">Choose Housecall Pro If:</h3>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-primary mt-0.5">→</span> You want review automation built in</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-primary mt-0.5">→</span> You need online booking on your website</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-primary mt-0.5">→</span> You want marketing tools without add-ons</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-primary mt-0.5">→</span> Your team is 4-10 technicians</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-primary mt-0.5">→</span> Total cost matters more than sticker price</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-border rounded-lg p-6 bg-white">
                  <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-lg mb-3">Choose Jobber If:</h3>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5">→</span> You want the simplest possible setup</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5">→</span> You are a solo operator or 1-3 tech team</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5">→</span> You want the best client-facing portal</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5">→</span> You already have review/marketing tools</li>
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="mt-0.5">→</span> Transparent pricing matters to you</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-10">
              <h2 class="font-heading font-semibold text-xl mb-3">What Neither Tool Does</h2>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Neither Housecall Pro nor Jobber includes built-in call tracking. If tracking inbound calls and lead sources is critical to your operation, consider <a href="/hvac/dispatch/best-dispatch-software-for-hvac" class="text-primary underline">Workiz</a> (which has a built-in phone system) or add <strong>CallRail</strong> as a separate integration.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-foreground/80 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Neither tool offers the depth of reporting and marketing attribution that ServiceTitan provides. If you need that level of data, see our <a href="/hvac/crm/servicetitan-alternatives" class="text-primary underline">ServiceTitan alternatives guide</a>.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div id="faq">
              
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8">
              <div class="cta-box">
  <h3>Try Housecall Pro Free</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-foreground)]/70 mb-4">Best total value when you factor in reviews and marketing.</p>
  <a href="#" class="cta-button" rel="sponsored nofollow" target="_blank">Learn More →</a>
</div>
              <div class="cta-box">
  <h3>Try Jobber Free</h3>
  <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-foreground)]/70 mb-4">Simplest setup. Best for solo operators and small teams.</p>
  <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/bo42cjptz4m2" class="cta-button" rel="sponsored nofollow" target="_blank">Learn More →</a>
</div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-border">
              <h3 class="data-label mb-3">Related Guides</h3>
              <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                <li><a href="/hvac/crm/best-crm-for-small-hvac-companies" class="text-primary hover:underline">Best CRM for Small HVAC Companies</a></li>
                <li><a href="/hvac/crm/servicetitan-alternatives" class="text-primary hover:underline">ServiceTitan Alternatives</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </article>

          <aside class="hidden lg:block w-64 flex-shrink-0">
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>

<!-- FAQ Section -->
<div id="faq" class="mt-10">
  <h2 class="font-semibold text-2xl mb-4" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="space-y-0">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Can I switch from Housecall Pro to Jobber (or vice versa)?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Yes. Both platforms support CSV data export and import. The migration typically takes 1-2 weeks including data transfer and team retraining.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Which has a better mobile app?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Both have strong mobile apps. Housecall Pro's app is slightly more feature-rich (includes review requests and marketing tools). Jobber's app is cleaner and faster for basic field operations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Do either offer call tracking?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Neither has built-in call tracking. Both integrate with CallRail and similar tools. If call tracking is critical, consider Workiz instead.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <p class="faq-question">Which is better for a plumbing company?</p>
      <p class="faq-answer">Both work well for plumbing. Jobber is slightly better for emergency/on-demand scheduling. Housecall Pro is better if you want automated review requests after jobs.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</ArticleLayout>
